article.headline: Morgan St. 81, Md-Eastern Shore 70
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Ronald Timus scored 19 points to lead five Morgan State players in double figures in an 81-70 victory Saturday over Maryland-Eastern Shore. Jamar Smith had 16 points, Joseph McLean had 13, Timothy Berkley added 12 and Boubacar Coly scored 11 for the Bears (11-15, 9-6 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Morgan State dominated inside, with 54 points in the paint compared to Maryland-Eastern Shore's 30. Reserve Corey Brown led the Hawks (3-24, 0-15 MEAC) with 22 points. Ed Tyson added 21 points, and Antonio McMillion had 16. The Bears began to take control just before halftime and led 39-30 at the half. Morgan State extended its lead to 17 on Timus' jumper with 14:55 remaining. The Hawks went on a 10-2 run to get within eight, but Morgan State took a 16-point lead again on Timus' dunk with eight minutes left.
